    	<title>Stream Video from the Raspberry Pi Camera to Web Browsers, Even on iOS and Android</title>
    	<dc:creator>Miguel Grinberg</dc:creator>
    	<link>http://blog.miguelgrinberg.com/post/stream-video-from-the-raspberry-pi-camera-to-web-browsers-even-on-ios-and-android</link>
    	<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/static/images/raspberry-pi-video-streaming-01.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/center&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#39;ve been excited about the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.raspberrypi.org/archives/3890&#34;&gt;Raspberry Pi Camera Module&lt;/a&gt; since it was announced last year, so I went and ordered one from &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.element14.com/community/groups/raspberry-pi-accessories?ICID=picamera-module-doc&#34;&gt;Element14&lt;/a&gt; as soon as it came on sale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have a few ideas for cool things to build with this camera and I will be blogging about them as I get to develop them. Today, I will show you how to transform the Raspberry Pi into a webcam server. You will be able to watch the video stream from the camera on any device that has a web browser. And yes, this includes the iPad/iPhone and Android devices!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
